The point to note here is that if you use the same instance of `SelectionManager` for multiple &quot;multi-selections&quot;, it will use the same mutex. On the other hand, a different `SelectionManager` instance will have its own mutex. This (or some variation on it) should enable you to fairly easily configure this over many tables in any way you need.

